<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-4D9B803A-BA12-4035-80B2-CFBB77288B40" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-4D9B803A-BA12-4035-80B2-CFBB77288B40" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Install a license via ORS</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="M148553-B105"><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> It is possible to receive a license through On Remote Service (ORS). (Instead of making the license request, requesting the back-office via mail and uploading the license manually). 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> How it works: 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Once there is an agreement regarding the license(s) requested, a product license number is registered in ILMS database. The updated licenses are transferred automatically via ORS to the engine. The administrator of the engine only needs to install and activate the updated licenses. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Installation</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-103ED4E7-FE4E-48E6-BC18-DBAE85CC3D4A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Install the license </title><table pgwide="1" id="GUID-21230E26-EF7E-48D1-80B2-D8426A6DA124" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" align="left" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="155.81pt" colwidth="10*" align="left" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="302.06pt" colwidth="90*" align="left" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Wait approximately 5 minutes after having received the license request. 
</p><note id="GUID-294E0871-361A-411A-9645-27FDEF727D40" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">the transfer of the updated license will take some time. 
</p></note></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Go to the Settings Editor: Support --&gt; Licenses --&gt; Licenses and click on "Install license from remote server". 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The following window appears: 
</p><fig id="GUID-D40C6BD1-34EF-4041-8F47-C849C858A827" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-F4BA5637-F084-46D5-9FAF-AE545CFD8D71-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-F4BA5637-F084-46D5-9FAF-AE545CFD8D71-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Click on "Install". 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">A warning "Restart" window will appear to warn that a Printer restart will be required to take into account the license. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Click on "OK" in this window. 
</p><fig id="GUID-6C0403AA-2BD5-4580-A487-2EC58D584E2A" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-77FED746-A52B-40CC-AF36-0ED144B6E560-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-77FED746-A52B-40CC-AF36-0ED144B6E560-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> A successful message will appear to confirm the license has been successfully installed. 
</p><fig id="GUID-16330AF1-5126-4A00-8ADF-EF6C99C518B3" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-B387BED3-25FA-44BF-B7A8-23C048BB5221-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-B387BED3-25FA-44BF-B7A8-23C048BB5221-low.png"/></fig><note id="GUID-B8649773-2629-412A-8DDB-CE9DA13B384F" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> The popup "restart the printer ... " does not result in a restart. This is a known issue. 
</p></note><note id="GUID-A9355F7D-1678-4035-8E38-44E5DB696A80" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> When the error appears "An unknown error has occurred", probably the license is not yet available on the system. 
</p></note></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Click OK in this window. Then restart the printer via the menu Support --&gt;Troubleshooting --&gt; Printer restart and job removal --&gt; Restart the system. 
</p><fig id="GUID-AB6BD99F-C8B0-4FEB-9B97-FA533650EFE0" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-09A0B8C4-A1C4-4F8C-9F8F-A6638859FF22-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-09A0B8C4-A1C4-4F8C-9F8F-A6638859FF22-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> After Restart, check the license(s) with the Settings Editor, Support --&gt; Licenses --&gt; Licenses: 
</p><fig id="GUID-49BA19A2-925A-4AC8-9BA2-A761D683EAE3" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-15866598-4392-4AC9-AE21-876B93E03C4B-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-15866598-4392-4AC9-AE21-876B93E03C4B-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-F431B0AC-C5BE-48D0-88B9-B2CC347FC3E4" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Known problems/Limitations</title><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> When an error occurs, you have an error message but no clue about the error possible cause(s) and what to do (See the troubleshooting section after this description). 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="00GENDIAG_ORS" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-831E43AD-1571-4EDD-9EF4-77BC0E2AF128.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text How to diagnose a license retrieval error when requesting the license from...?>How to diagnose a license retrieval error when requesting the license from ORS</xref>
</p></li></ul></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-7D3F358C-1AB9-4A5D-9B0E-C75D689F152E.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Installation</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>